                ][styleclass="page-content"][
                
                    ]Hey there! I've been technically playing PFQ since 2023, but honestly, I know next to nothing, haha. When I first joined, I thought the journaling feature of the site was so neat, and it's definitely helped me get back into the game after so long.[
                    ][br][br][
                    ]However, I did stay true to my word, and I am slowly making my journal prettier! I'm really excited about it, actually, haha. I hope you all enjoy your stay here at my little cozy hovel as much as I enjoyed creating it.[
                    ][br][br][
                    ]As before, I am looking for friends to trade and help best I can. I hope to open a shop soon, as well as a codex! We'll see how this goes.[
                    ][br][br][
                    
                    ][h2][u]About Me[/u][/h2][
                    ][br][
                    ][b]Name:[/b] Andi / Socio[br][
                    ][b]Pronouns:[/b] They / Them[br][
                    ][b]Sexuality:[/b] Queer[br][
                    ][b]Age:[/b] 24[br][
                    
                    ][br][
                    ]I am a recent computer science graduate (should totally check out my thesis) dealing with the job-search grind. Since I work in education, I honestly don't expect to get a second job until the spring. I have another part-time job where I teach remote, but the hours are limited, so I'll prolly be pretty active here again for a while.[
                    ][br][br][
                    ]I love teaching! And I love programming! Unfortunately, that's a huge chunk of my personality, haha. My favorite content to teach is game development tutorials, but I also teach AP Computer Science and other CS courses on a K-12 level. My research is focused on using game development as a medium to teach computer science![
                    ][br][br][
                    
                    ][h2][u]Interests[/u][/h2][
                    ][br][
                    ]In my free time, I obviously like to play and watch Pokemon. I'm super excited for the Legends game, even if it may be not that good. I watch a lot of YouTube, podcasts like Creep Cast and the Lore Lodge, Wendigoon, Leon Lush, Game Grumps, and occasionally classic gaming YouTubers. I also really enjoy a long-form video essay once in a while about obscure subjects.[
                    ][br][br][
                    ]I also love to program. Yes, for fun lol. I have a couple game development projects up my sleeve that I'd like to release one day - maybe in the next couple of years. I also have a pet-site I've been developing for a few years, not sure if it'll ever be publlic, but it's a fun exercise.[
                    ][br][br][
                    ]I occasionally do art, but not as often as I did when I was in art school (keep in mind my DeviantArt has some pretty outdated stuff). I clearly also have been spending a lot of time on PokeFarm, haha. It keeps me busy and doesn't drain my energy, so it's a nice past time (as many of my hobbies are mentally exhausting). I also like to do puzzle/logic games, like sudoku and nonograms. :>[
                    ][br][br][
                    ]Anyway, that's enough about me! Click on the tabs to navigate around this journal and enjoy your stay![
                    
